texts.text: Are you even listening? Hey, don't ignore me...!
Ah c'mon, don't give me that look...
>Not to you, but something in the distance,
>From beyond the horizon of the ruined landscape,
>something, like a mirage, starts to envelop your field of view,
>In a flash, everything is warped and consumed by an overwhelming wave...
Fancy seeing you in Hell. How'd you end up here?
T-this is Hell...? Wait, but this is Tokyo...?
>Pixie looks to the red sky and cratered landscape.
>But the surviving buildings are that of Tokyo.
Well, whatever. It's been a while, but human's back on the menu!
Uhh, hey! Would you kindly Devil Download a little faster!
>The Devil Downloading App keeps spitting out an error message.
>You manage to block Vetala's attack with your shield.
>You notice in your hand the sword that just cut down your enemy.
You can't really Devil Download all that easily.
And you're getting maybe one demon after messing with the settings.
But you don't look so hot either.
I wonder why... I feel just fine.
And that red sky. Maybe it's...
>You see visible signs of the laws of physics unraveling.
>Earth and rubble begin rising to the sky.
The same thing happened to my world...
The Fairy King said it goes "beyond the Dragon Stream".
Your world and Hell are connected to each other now.
At this rate, this place will be consumed by Hell,
The whole world hasn't been consumed yet,
but only this place for now.
If we deal with the "root" of this problem, things will return to normal.
We have to figure out what that is,
and it could be the strongest demon here or something.
>Vanitas caused countless souls to be returned to the Dragon Stream.
>High levels of traffic and pollution in the Dragon Stream.
>You surmise this may be a possible cause.
>The red sky, constant thunder and floating earth...
>You start to think this world is seeking its own destruction...
>As if it's in its death throes, begging with its last whispers.
The "physical world" being joined with Hell
is causing this world's "laws" to break down...
Not being able to Devil Download,
and your lack of power might be a symptom of this.
Get out of here if things get too crazy!
(So it's either Hell in Tokyo or some kind of purgatory. Great...)
